[{"detection_name": "LLM: Introspection", "detection": "potential", "category": "Injection Attacks", "description": "The GraphQL API is returning descriptive schema/validation errors that reveal internal type and field names (e.g., Query.sets and type Set). This is an information-disclosure form of introspection: even without using the formal __schema introspection query, an attacker can infer schema structure from these error messages and iteratively enumerate fields/types to discover sensitive endpoints and craft targeted queries. While no direct data leak is shown here, the exposure of schema details materially increases attack surface.
